  "_comment": "Vision OS 3.0 weekly-routine profile (System/run.ps1 passes this via --settings for the weekly run ONLY; nightly/morning use headless.json with no MCP at all). Approved by the owner 2026-06-11 (desk/proposals.md): the weekly run gets ENUMERATED READ-ONLY connector tools so prediction outcomes can be scored unattended. Everything else is identical to the no-egress profile: web tools and network shell verbs denied, writes scoped to Vault/, rail files untouchable, ledgers closed (close record stages at Vault/desk/.run-close-<run_id>.json). The weekly launches WITHOUT --strict-mcp-config so user-scope connectors load; in -p mode any tool not allowed here is refused - the absence of a rule is a closed gate. Write/send/mutation tool names on the same servers are ALSO explicitly denied as belt-and-braces. Correction of record (2026-06-11, weekly run 070418): Ahrefs/GSC and HubSpot ARE reachable headless - the first probe misread an allow-list gap as invisibility. Their read tools were allow-listed 2026-06-11 after attended confirmation (HubSpot auth live; Ahrefs authorized and project-scoped, though the GSC data link was not yet feeding - reads fail soft as reported debt until the owner's GSC revisit). HubSpot appears under two possible casings; both are listed, the wrong one is inert.",
